==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinxit
<hw>Pinx"it</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., perfect indicative 3d sing.
of <ets>pingere</ets> to paint.]</ety> <def>A word appended to the
artist's name or initials on a painting, or engraved copy of a painting;
<as>as, <ex>Rubens pinxit</ex>, Rubens painted (this)</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinxter</ent>⟦br⟧
